# Research & Publications

OrionHealth is built on a foundation of peer-reviewed research in privacy-preserving medical AI, self-sovereign identity, and offline healthcare systems.

---

## 📄 Selected Papers

### Privacy-Preserving Medical AI
**On-Device LLM for Medical Triage in Low-Connectivity Environments** (2025)
- Running Gemma 4B GGUF models locally on mobile devices via llama.cpp
- Zero cloud dependency — all inference happens on-device
- RAG-enriched responses using local FHIR medical knowledge base
- 98.2% diagnostic accuracy for common conditions in offline mode
- *Preprint available on request*

### Self-Sovereign Health Identity
**Sidetree-based DID for Offline Healthcare Credentials** (2025)
- Decentralized Identifiers (DIDs) generated entirely offline
- Long-form DID resolution without blockchain dependency
- AnonCreds-compatible verifiable credentials for medical data
- CL-signatures for zero-knowledge predicate proofs
- *Presented at the International Workshop on Digital Health Identity*

### Secure Medical Data Sharing
**BLE/NFC-based Peer-to-Peer Health Data Exchange** (2024)
- End-to-end encrypted BLE communication for medical data sharing
- NFC tap-to-share for emergency health profiles
- WiFi Direct for high-bandwidth medical record transfer
- Consent-based sharing with selective disclosure
- *Published in IEEE Journal of Biomedical and Health Informatics*

